race.comment: DERELICT (2) missed the placings two runs back then improved last start but found one better over 1000m at Bairnsdale, beaten one length after being in the firing line on the turn. Finds a suitable race and can play a major role. BOUDICA WARRIOR (9) raced below her best last time when seventh over 1000m at Bendigo, beaten 1.75 lengths after being prominent at the bend. Finds a nice race and can make amends. BRONCO REVOLUTION (8) is struggling to break through but hasn't been far away, the latest effort a fifth beaten 1.5 lengths over 1000m at Bendigo. Jake Duffy goes well on this four-year-old and is back on top today. WAR OF WISDOM (10) races predominantly at the picnics but will be better for the first up run and might benefit from Craig Newitt hopping aboard.
